original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses ANSI escape codes, specifically the sequence `\033[32m` followed by your desired text and ending with the reset code `\033[0m`. For instance:

```
\033[32mHello, Green World!\033[0m
```

When this line is printed to a terminal supporting ANSI escape codes, it will display "Hello, Green World!" in green color. Note that this solution assumes the terminal emulator being used interprets the ANSI escape codes correctly.
